    {
      "id": "SKNzDnMWeP9BsqkhfOzYP",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1.3745432371360948,
      "y": -18517.246232590467,
      "width": 2942.458740234375,
      "height": 675,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b65",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1564189187,
      "version": 1685,
      "versionNonce": 361472739,
      "isDeleted": true,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776868783858,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Leetcode is not just about contest or Solving a problem it is also about registering a User, bringing the user at very first point of time at plateform taking the\npayment from them apart from this Leetcode also has some Lecture aspects like we can learn something from Leetcode as well\n\nwhy we are discussing this -> Due to Leetcode or any other application is not just about one or two features  it is made up of multiple set of feature all together\n    now during the time of extreme load may be not every single aspect of our application will face a humoungous amount of load\n\nLIke do we feel any contest that is happen, On the day of contest do we think we are going to see very abnormal scale at payment module probably not we might can\nsee a little bit of spike\n\nMay be Signup Registration will increase on general leetcode contest but not too much we might see bit of spike here and there thats it\n\nthe problem is that if we will put all the logic in one place and lets say we have horizontally scale our Application server then we are also also scaling the code modules\nthat don't need this much amount of scaling we dont need to scale our registration system or Payment system\nOnly the submission and Evaluation system where the code will be evaluated that need to be scale during the contest so that comes into new topic understanding new\ntopic Monolyth and Microservice Infrastructure",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Leetcode is not just about contest or Solving a problem it is also about registering a User, bringing the user at very first point of time at plateform taking the\npayment from them apart from this Leetcode also has some Lecture aspects like we can learn something from Leetcode as well\n\nwhy we are discussing this -> Due to Leetcode or any other application is not just about one or two features  it is made up of multiple set of feature all together\n    now during the time of extreme load may be not every single aspect of our application will face a humoungous amount of load\n\nLIke do we feel any contest that is happen, On the day of contest do we think we are going to see very abnormal scale at payment module probably not we might can\nsee a little bit of spike\n\nMay be Signup Registration will increase on general leetcode contest but not too much we might see bit of spike here and there thats it\n\nthe problem is that if we will put all the logic in one place and lets say we have horizontally scale our Application server then we are also also scaling the code modules\nthat don't need this much amount of scaling we dont need to scale our registration system or Payment system\nOnly the submission and Evaluation system where the code will be evaluated that need to be scale during the contest so that comes into new topic understanding new\ntopic Monolyth and Microservice Infrastructure",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
