      "text": "Why Python, when we have C, C++, Java etc ->",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Why Python, when we have C, C++, Java etc ->",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "hl004f9g8mw7FEGmKTc7L",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1037.5582728643537,
      "y": -13847.443043342248,
      "width": 1155,
      "height": 575,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9A",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1032568173,
      "version": 984,
      "versionNonce": 1319557763,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776870218662,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Python used everywhere\n    IOT\n    ML\n    Scraping\n    Website development\n    Hacking\n\nhence python exists in almost every domain.\n\nPython by default is installed in our Linux machine, whether it can be Ubuntu VM in our machine or\nin a cloud machine, Python will be by default installed\n\n\nWe need to have Jupyter notebook or Anaconda(framework of Python) setup that will be good for us\ninstall it for next class, due to for ML some part we will do in Anaconda only.\n\nFOr now go to linux terminal\n\nsudo su -> root user\npython -> now prompt changes and we enter a mode of python which is called as REPL(Read Event Print Loop)\n1+2 -> 3 -> Read eval Print will happen in Loop, Loop means it is ready for next command and it will Read\n             eval and print and so on\n        we are using REPL to understand the impact of each and every line.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Python used everywhere\n    IOT\n    ML\n    Scraping\n    Website development\n    Hacking\n\nhence python exists in almost every domain.\n\nPython by default is installed in our Linux machine, whether it can be Ubuntu VM in our machine or\nin a cloud machine, Python will be by default installed\n\n\nWe need to have Jupyter notebook or Anaconda(framework of Python) setup that will be good for us\ninstall it for next class, due to for ML some part we will do in Anaconda only.\n\nFOr now go to linux terminal\n\nsudo su -> root user\npython -> now prompt changes and we enter a mode of python which is called as REPL(Read Event Print Loop)\n1+2 -> 3 -> Read eval Print will happen in Loop, Loop means it is ready for next command and it will Read\n             eval and print and so on\n        we are using REPL to understand the impact of each and every line.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "g5muLxGcEjbpvyF6xRfDG",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1027.7564215146597,
      "y": -13190.848086713704,
      "width": 594,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b9B",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 137173997,
      "version": 66,
      "versionNonce": 1226976845,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776870264548,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What is the smallest part of the Programming Language?",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
