      "seed": 1201748909,
      "version": 1492,
      "versionNonce": 734783651,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776873489924,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "whenever we run our code, code or data is in our RAM(primary memory), even varialbes get\ncreated when the code is executed not when we save the file of code.\nwhen the code is executed, means it becomes a running process which means it is in our \nRAM, so varialbes are created over there\n\na = 10, here 10 is constant, a is variable\n\nwhat is the type of constant we are puting inside memory that type is become type of\nour variable also, it is called datatype.\n\na = 10\ntype(a) -> <class 'int'>\ndir(a) -> since a is of integer, it will take us to the directory of a integer, that what all\n        things we can do with a integer.\n\na = 'rahul'\ndir(a)\na.lower() # this willl not going to chagne original due to it is immutable\na = a.lower() -> if we want to change\na.strip() -> it will remove all spaces from left and right nothing from middle\na.strip('*') -> from left and right * gone\na.lstrip() -> remove space from left\na.rstrip() -> from right remove space\n\na = \"amit***\"\nQ -> remove last 2 *\na = a.rstrip('**') -> amit\na = a + '*'\n\n\n'', \"\", '''''', \"\"\"\"\"\" -> all are strings\n\n\"\"\" is used for multi line string\n\n\na = \"Hi Geeta, How are you\"\n>>> a.split() -> output will be list\n['Hi', 'Geeta,', 'How', 'are', 'you']",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "whenever we run our code, code or data is in our RAM(primary memory), even varialbes get\ncreated when the code is executed not when we save the file of code.\nwhen the code is executed, means it becomes a running process which means it is in our \nRAM, so varialbes are created over there\n\na = 10, here 10 is constant, a is variable\n\nwhat is the type of constant we are puting inside memory that type is become type of\nour variable also, it is called datatype.\n\na = 10\ntype(a) -> <class 'int'>\ndir(a) -> since a is of integer, it will take us to the directory of a integer, that what all\n        things we can do with a integer.\n\na = 'rahul'\ndir(a)\na.lower() # this willl not going to chagne original due to it is immutable\na = a.lower() -> if we want to change\na.strip() -> it will remove all spaces from left and right nothing from middle\na.strip('*') -> from left and right * gone\na.lstrip() -> remove space from left\na.rstrip() -> from right remove space\n\na = \"amit***\"\nQ -> remove last 2 *\na = a.rstrip('**') -> amit\na = a + '*'\n\n\n'', \"\", '''''', \"\"\"\"\"\" -> all are strings\n\n\"\"\" is used for multi line string\n\n\na = \"Hi Geeta, How are you\"\n>>> a.split() -> output will be list\n['Hi', 'Geeta,', 'How', 'are', 'you']",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
