      "updated": 1776878886431,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "import os\nimport subprocess as sp\n\nthese will help us to script our Linux commands, first of all it is not only Linux commands that we \nscript, we can script almost anything, we can automate almost anything. we can script or automate, when\nscript is running on a trigger then it is called as automation, so we can kind of script our AWS\nresource creation, GCP resource creation or deletion or configuration management which is something\nthat we will be doing very frequently, we can script our monitoring, we can script starting of a task\nat a particular time almost anything like this we can try to put it in a file and script, most often\nchoosed programming language for this purpose is Python.\n\nOne thing is we can do scripting in Bash, If we talk about Linux scripting, we can write a bash script\nor a shell script, Why it is not preferred or why people are moving away from it or have been moving\naway from it for a very long time now, because the crux is when we script something we get the data of \na command based on that data now we have to take certain decisions, which means data is again a string\nand when we get a string and we have to take some decisions, so one thing is on whole string we need \nto take some decision, but at time we need to fetch some specific words and then understand the meaning\nof those words, try to have a loop on them or try to have ML algo on them or something like that, and \nthen take a final decision of what is the next command, like should our next command be a or b  that is\nvery tricky, now in that case, advance language like Python and all, they help us to deal with the output",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "import os\nimport subprocess as sp\n\nthese will help us to script our Linux commands, first of all it is not only Linux commands that we \nscript, we can script almost anything, we can automate almost anything. we can script or automate, when\nscript is running on a trigger then it is called as automation, so we can kind of script our AWS\nresource creation, GCP resource creation or deletion or configuration management which is something\nthat we will be doing very frequently, we can script our monitoring, we can script starting of a task\nat a particular time almost anything like this we can try to put it in a file and script, most often\nchoosed programming language for this purpose is Python.\n\nOne thing is we can do scripting in Bash, If we talk about Linux scripting, we can write a bash script\nor a shell script, Why it is not preferred or why people are moving away from it or have been moving\naway from it for a very long time now, because the crux is when we script something we get the data of \na command based on that data now we have to take certain decisions, which means data is again a string\nand when we get a string and we have to take some decisions, so one thing is on whole string we need \nto take some decision, but at time we need to fetch some specific words and then understand the meaning\nof those words, try to have a loop on them or try to have ML algo on them or something like that, and \nthen take a final decision of what is the next command, like should our next command be a or b  that is\nvery tricky, now in that case, advance language like Python and all, they help us to deal with the output",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
